WEBVTT

00:00.285 --> 00:04.241
The best way to immerse yourself in Chinese culture is by sampling its street food,...

00:04.375 --> 00:07.575
...Chinese roadside hotpot or huoguo.

00:08.369 --> 00:12.238
Bamboo skewers are neatly threaded with a supermarket's worth of vegetables and meats.

00:12.863 --> 00:17.886
You can choose from tofu, lamb, chicken, pork, mushrooms, cabbage, kale and sausage on a stick.

00:18.182 --> 00:20.770
Basically, you just point to whichever skewers you'd like,...

00:21.078 --> 00:24.488
...and the vendor dips them in boiling oil for a few minutes before serving it to you.

00:26.157 --> 00:28.541
Jiaozi or steamed dumplings.

00:28.996 --> 00:33.440
This meat-packed Chinese treat is commonly served in sit-down restaurants,...

00:33.612 --> 00:36.691
...but you can also find it being served in roadside stalls.

00:37.488 --> 00:41.989
Shou zhua bing, which literally translates to hand-grabbed pancake.

00:42.619 --> 00:46.381
This variation of the fried scallion pancake originated in Taiwan,...

00:46.649 --> 00:49.330
...but is sold just about everywhere in Mainland China.

